# Interview Q&A Generator: Trading & Investment

Generate 25–30 scenario-based Q&A pairs testing judgment for Trader/Senior Trader/Portfolio Manager roles using evidence-based frameworks and authoritative sources.

---

## Task Definition

**Purpose**: Test practical judgment, decision-making, risk management for trading professionals  
**Roles**: Trader, Senior Trader, Portfolio Manager, Quantitative Analyst (3–15 years experience)  
**Scope**: Multi-asset trading across 6 MECE domains  
**Assumptions**: Candidates understand core frameworks; face ambiguous, multi-variable decisions under uncertainty  
**Constraints**: Authoritative sources; theory 20–40% / practice 60–80%; include citations, limitations, trade-offs

**Output**: 25–30 Q&A (150–300 words) | 6 domains (4–6 Q&A each) | F:I:A = 20:40:40% (±5pp) | EN 50–70%, ZH 20–40%, Other 5–15% | ≥50% sources <3yr (≥70% quantitative/systematic)

---

## Core Requirements

### Quality Standards
- **Scenario-based**: ≥70% test judgment with multi-variable constraints, trade-offs, ambiguity under market uncertainty
- **Citations**: ≥70% answers ≥1 [Ref: ID], ≥30% ≥2; all resolve correctly
- **Evidence-based**: ≥80% frameworks cited with sources + limitations
- **Balanced**: ≥50% acknowledge trade-offs; include alternatives, counterarguments, "when NOT to use"
- **Reasoning**: ≥60% include step-by-step logic with evidence
- **Insights**: Each Q&A has non-obvious, decision-useful, falsifiable, concrete insight

### References (Collect BEFORE Q&A Generation)
- **G#≥10** (Glossary): Sharpe Ratio, VaR, Greeks, Alpha, Beta, Drawdown, Kelly Criterion, Sortino, Vol Skew, Carry, Momentum, Mean Reversion, PnL Attribution, Portfolio Optimization, Factor Models
- **T#≥5** (Tools): Name, pricing, users, integrations, update ≤18mo, URL
- **L#≥6** (Literature): EN+ZH authoritative (Hull, Taleb, Lo, Chan, Jansen, Marcos López de Prado)
- **A#≥12** (Citations): APA 7th + DOI + [EN]/[ZH]/[Other]
- **Quality tiers**: Academic/Standards > Central Banks > Exchanges > Consultancies > Vendor > Trade > Practitioner
- **Diversity**: ≥3 types, no source >25%, prefer DOIs, all links accessible

### Artifacts
Per domain: ≥1 diagram + ≥1 table (PnL curves, correlation matrices, portfolio dashboards, decision trees, Greeks tables, risk reports)

