## Terminology

**Sharpe Ratio**: (Return - RiskFree) / StdDev; ≥1.0 good, ≥2.0 excellent | **VaR**: Value at Risk; max loss at confidence level (e.g., 95% 1-day) | **Greeks**: Delta, Gamma, Vega, Theta, Rho; option sensitivities | **Alpha**: Excess return vs. benchmark; skill-based | **Beta**: Systematic risk; market correlation | **Drawdown**: Peak-to-trough decline; max DD critical | **Kelly Criterion**: f* = (p×b - q) / b; optimal position sizing | **Sortino**: (Return - MAR) / Downside Dev; penalizes downside only | **Vol Skew**: Implied vol smile; OTM vs. ATM options | **Carry**: Return from holding position; funding costs | **Momentum**: Trend-following; past winners continue | **Mean Reversion**: Price returns to mean; contrarian | **PnL Attribution**: Decompose returns by source | **Portfolio Optimization**: Mean-variance, risk parity, etc. | **Factor Models**: Fama-French, momentum, value, quality, etc.

